HEADWORD: Overslip
<hw>O`ver*slip"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To slip or
slide over; to pass easily or carelessly beyond; to omit; to neglect;
<as>as, to <ex>overslip</ex> time or opportunity</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

